#  Grocery Booking System

A production-ready Grocery Booking System backend built with **Node.js, Express, PostgreSQL, and Prisma**.  
It supports authentication, role-based access control, inventory management, and order processing with transactional safety.

---

## Features

-  Authentication & Authorization (JWT + Role-based access)
-  Admin panel for grocery item management (CRUD)
-  User features: browse items & place orders
-  Transaction-safe order processing (Prisma transactions)
-  Security: Helmet, CORS, Rate limiting, Input validation
-  Scalable modular architecture
-  Winston logging with file rotation
-  Swagger API documentation

---

##  Tech Stack

- Node.js 20
- Express.js
- PostgreSQL
- Prisma ORM
- Docker & Docker Compose
- JWT Authentication
- Winston Logger
- Joi Validation

---

##  Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in root:

```env
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@postgres:5432/grocery_db?schema=public"

JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d

ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
ADMIN_PASSWORD=Admin@123456
ADMIN_NAME=Super Admin

RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=900000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=100

LOG_LEVEL=info
 Run with Docker (Recommended)
1️ Start the application
docker compose up --build

This will:

Start PostgreSQL database
Start Node.js backend server
2️ Run database migration

Open a new terminal and run:

npx prisma migrate dev --name init

This will:

Create all database tables
Apply Prisma schema changes
3️ Restart Docker containers

Stop running containers:

Ctrl + C

Then restart:

docker compose up
4️ Access the application
API Base URL:
http://localhost:3000
Swagger API Docs:
http://localhost:3000/api-docs
 Quick Start Summary
docker compose up --build
npx prisma migrate dev --name init
docker compose up
 Project Structure
src/
 ├── config/
 ├── controllers/
 ├── middlewares/
 ├── routes/
 ├── services/
 ├── utils/
 └── app.js
Testing

You can test APIs using:

Swagger UI
Postman
Curl
 Notes
Make sure Docker is running before starting
.env file must be properly configured
First admin is created via environment variables
Prisma migration must run at least once before using APIs